Nigerian senator, Shehu Sani, has taken to social media to call out his colleague, Senator Ademola Adeleke, following how he likes to dance on different occasions, as he stated that the governorship aspirant’s style of dancing is a valuable resource that can draw the attentions of tourists to Osun State, Nigeria.
With the forthcoming 2023 Osun State governorship election that is set to hold in less than few weeks from now, the governorship candidates of the different political parties across the country are all getting themselves ready to ensure that they occupy such position.
However, incumbent governor of the state and 2023 governorship candidate under the ruling APC party, Gboyega Oyetola, had earlier on, spoken about his opponent, Senator Ademola Adeleke’s dancing steps, as he stated that governance is not a dancing competition, adding that it needs God’s wisdom which he has.
Former Kaduna state governorship election, Shehu Sani, has also taken to social media to talk about the dancing steps of his colleague, Ademola Adeleke, as he stated that the dancing steps of the governorship candidate is an asset that can attract tourists to Osun State.
